go_data.justification: Alpha-1-antitrypsin blocks SARS-CoV-2 infection of Vero E6 cells by blocking the processing of SARS-CoV-2 S protein.
Alpha-1-antitrypsin is enriched in ChipEXOs, which are exosomes.
Alpha-1-antitrypsin blocks the processing of SARS-CoV-2 S protein by furin and the transmembrane serine protease TMPRSS2.
